      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are looking kind of sickly. the leaves on the bottom are turning yellow and falling off. what do you think is going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a common issue with tomato plants. It sounds like your plants may be experiencing a case of \"bottom-blight\" or \"legginess\", where the lower leaves are yellowing and dropping off due to a lack of light, possibly from being shaded by nearby plants. This can be a challenge to address, but try pruning the lower leaves to improve air circulation and increase sunlight for the rest of the plant. You can also consider rearranging the surrounding plants to give your tomatoes more direct sunlight.",
