      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're thinking of a pest or disease that's causing nutrient leaching or scavenging. One possibility is that slugs or snails are burrowing into the soil, eating away at the roots and breaking down organic matter. These pests can also contribute to nutrient deficiencies by consuming plant tissues and excreting waste that can alter soil chemistry. If you have a high humidity or moist environment, you may also be attracting pests like fungus gnats or caterpillars that can feed on plant tissues and disrupt nutrient availability.",
      "source": "target",
